1. Introduction
Argan oil extracted from the fruits of
Argania spinosa
L.
(Sapotaceae) has many nutritional, cosmetic, and therapeutic
properties thanks to its richness in unsaturated fatty acids
(UFA) and bioactive substances such as tocopherols and
phytosterols [1]. Th ecosmeti coi li sextracte db ymechanical
press from unroasted almonds. As for the edible oil, it is
extracted by press or in the traditional way by hand kneading
roasted almonds. Roasting is usually carried out on the wood
